  "prompt": "Which books are preferred by 12 board topper?",
  "response": "Students who achieve top scores in their Class 12 board exams often follow a combination of NCERT textbooks and additional reference materials to enhance their understanding. Here are some commonly preferred books across different subjects:\n\n### Science:\n\n1. **Physics:**\n   - NCERT Physics textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Concepts of Physics by H.C. Verma**\n   - **Fundamentals of Physics by David Halliday, Robert Resnick**\n\n2. **Chemistry:**\n   - NCERT Chemistry textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Physical Chemistry by O.P. Tandon**\n   - **Organic Chemistry by Morrison and Boyd**\n\n3. **Biology:**\n   - NCERT Biology textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Biology by Trueman**\n   - **Objective Biology by Dinesh**\n\n### Mathematics:\n\n1. **NCERT Mathematics textbooks for Class 12**\n2. **R.D. Sharma \u2013 Mathematics for Class 12**\n3. **Cengage Mathematics Series**\n\n### Commerce:\n\n1. **Accountancy:**\n   - NCERT Accountancy textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Accountancy by D.K. Goel**\n\n2. **Business Studies:**\n   - NCERT Business Studies textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Business Studies by Poonam Gandhi**\n\n3. **Economics:**\n   - NCERT Economics textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Statistics for Economics by R.S. Bhardwaj**\n\n### Arts:\n\n1. **History:**\n   - NCERT History textbooks for Class 12\n   - **History of Modern India by Bipan Chandra**\n\n2. **Political Science:**\n   - NCERT Political Science textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Indian Government and Politics by Shivani Ghosh**\n\n3. **Literature:**\n   - NCERT English textbooks for Class 12\n   - **Woven Words by K.V. Sreeram**\n\n### Study Tips:\n- **Practice Previous Year Papers:** Solving past year question papers helps in understanding the exam pattern.\n- **Regular Revision:** Regularly revisiting concepts helps reinforce learning.\n- **Time Management:** Creating a study schedule that allocates time for each subject.\n- **Online Resources:** Utilizing online platforms for additional practice and resources.\n\nWhile these are some of the preferred books, the right choice may vary depending on individual learning styles and preferences.",
